{"title_page": "Peter Daniels (racing driver)", "text_new": "{{short description|American racing driver|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n'''Peter Daniels''' is an American [[racing driver]] who won the [[NASCAR]] [[Whelen All-American Series|Weekly Series]] national championship in 2002.<ref name=\"StarsBorn_Daniels\">Schaefer, Paul.  ''Where Stars Are Born: Celebrating 25 Years of NASCAR Weekly Racing''.  Coastal 181, Newburyport, Massachusetts, USA, 2006.  {{ISBN|0-9789261-0-2}}.  pp. 137-142.</ref>\n\nIn 2002, driving an asphalt Modified owned by his brother Richard Daniels, Peter won 14 of the 18 races that he entered at [[Claremont, New Hampshire|Claremont]] Speedway (now named Twin State Speedway) in New Hampshire.<ref name=\"StarsBorn_Daniels\" />\n\nDaniels won Claremont's Pro Stock division championships in 1993, 1994, 1996, 1998, and 1999.  He won the same track's Modified championships in 1999, 2001, and 2002.<ref name=\"StarsBorn_Daniels\" />\n\nHe raced in the [[Busch East Series]] in 1991 through 1993.<ref name=\"StarsBorn_Daniels\" />\n\n== References ==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n* {{Racing-Reference driver|Peter_Daniels}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Daniels, Peter}}\n[[Category:NASCAR drivers]]\n[[Category:American racing drivers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n\n\n{{NASCAR-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American racing driver|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n'''Peter Daniels''' is an American [[racing driver]] who won the [[NASCAR]] Weekly Series national championship in 2002.<ref name=\"StarsBorn_Daniels\">Schaefer, Paul.  ''Where Stars Are Born: Celebrating 25 Years of NASCAR Weekly Racing''.  Coastal 181, Newburyport, Massachusetts, USA, 2006.  {{ISBN|0-9789261-0-2}}.  pp. 137-142.</ref>\n\nIn 2002, driving an asphalt Modified owned by his brother Richard Daniels, Peter won 14 of the 18 races that he entered at [[Claremont, New Hampshire|Claremont]] Speedway (now named Twin State Speedway) in New Hampshire.<ref name=\"StarsBorn_Daniels\" />\n\nDaniels won Claremont's Pro Stock division championships in 1993, 1994, 1996, 1998, and 1999.  He won the same track's Modified championships in 1999, 2001, and 2002.<ref name=\"StarsBorn_Daniels\" />\n\nHe raced in the [[Busch East Series]] in 1991 through 1993.<ref name=\"StarsBorn_Daniels\" />\n\n== References ==\n<references/>\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Daniels, Peter}}\n[[Category:NASCAR drivers]]\n[[Category:American racing drivers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n\n\n{{NASCAR-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Luks25", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peter_Daniels_(racing_driver)"}
{"title_page": "Mahbubul Alam (politician)", "text_new": "{{short description|Bangladeshi Politician}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name                = Mahbubul Alam\n| office              = Member of Bangladesh Parliament\n| term_start          = 1988\n| term_end            = 1990\n| predecessor         = [[Moin Uddin Ahmed]]\n| successor           = [[Shahjahan Miah]]\n| birth_date          = \n| birth_place         = \n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| party               = \n| bodyclass           = \n| mainwidth           = \n| native_name         = \u09ae\u09be\u09b9\u09ac\u09c1\u09ac\u09c1\u09b2 \u0986\u09b2\u09ae\n| native_name_lang    = bn\n}}\n'''Mahbubul Alam''' is a Bangladeshi politician in [[Chapai Nawabganj District]]. He was elected a member of parliament from [[Chapai Nawabganj-1]] in [[1988 Bangladeshi general election|1988]].<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=http://www.parliament.gov.bd/images/pdf/formermp/4th.pdf|title=\"List of 4th Parliament Members\"|publisher=Bangladesh Parliament (in Bengali).|accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nAlam was elected to parliament from [[Chapai Nawabganj-1]] in [[1988 Bangladeshi general election]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}{{Bangladesh-politician-stub}}\n\n[[Category:People from Chapai Nawabganj district]]\n[[Category:3rd Jatiya Sangsad members]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Bangladeshi Politician}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name                = Mahbubul Alam\n| office              = Member of Bangladesh Parliament\n| term_start          = 1988\n| term_end            = 1990\n| predecessor         = [[Moin Uddin Ahmed]]\n| successor           = [[Shahjahan Miah]]\n| birth_date          = \n| birth_place         = \n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| party               = \n| bodyclass           = \n| mainwidth           = \n| native_name         = \u09ae\u09be\u09b9\u09ac\u09c1\u09ac\u09c1\u09b2 \u0986\u09b2\u09ae\n| native_name_lang    = bn\n}}\n'''Mahbubul Alam''' [[Bangladeshis|Bangladeshi]] Politician in [[Chapai Nawabganj District]]. He was elected a member of parliament from [[Chapai Nawabganj-1]] in [[1988 Bangladeshi general election|1988]].<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=http://www.parliament.gov.bd/images/pdf/formermp/4th.pdf|title=\"List of 4th Parliament Members\"|publisher=Bangladesh Parliament (in Bengali).|accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nMahbubul Alam was elected to parliament from [[Chapai Nawabganj-1]] in [[1988 Bangladeshi general election]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}{{Bangladesh-politician-stub}}\n\n[[Category:People from Chapai Nawabganj district]]\n[[Category:3rd Jatiya Sangsad members]]\n", "name_user": "Lopifalko", "label": "safe", "comment": "MOS:COMMONWORDS+WP:SURNAME+ copyedit", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mahbubul_Alam_(politician)"}
